cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA, cs.SI 

This paper deals with image processing and segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces novel norms defined in different functional Banach spaces, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the decomposition of images into multiple meaningful components, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a generalized notion of segmentation, which is related to signal processing (cs.SI).
